Introduction

Zhou Jie Qiong (formerly known as Kyulkyung) is a Chinese dancer, singer-songwriter, composer, and actress under Zhou Jieqiong Studio. She is a former member of the girl group PRISTIN, its sub-unit PRISTIN V, and the project girl group I.O.I.

She made her solo China-based debut with the digital single "Why" on September 6, 2018.

In 2016, Zhou Jie Qiong participated in Mnet's survival television show, Produce 101, along with other five trainees from her agency, Pledis Entertainment. She and Nayoung were the only ones to make it to the final lineup, ranking 6th and 10th respectively, becoming members of the girl group I.O.I.

On May 4, 2016, she debuted in I.O.I with the mini album, Chrysalis, and its title track, "Dream Girls".

After the disbandment of I.O.I on January 29, 2017, Pledis announced that Zhou Jie Qiong and Nayoung would debut together with their former Produce 101 contestants, as members of PRISTIN, which debuted on March 21, 2017, with the mini album Hi! PRISTIN and its title track, "Wee Woo".

In 2018, the agency formed PRISTIN's first sub-unit, PRISTIN V, with Zhou Jie Qiong being one of its members. They debuted on May 28 with the single album, "Like a V".

On September 2019, Zhou Jie Qiong sent a contract termination notice to Pledis and XCSS Entertainment, her Chinese agency, which led them to demand her for breaching the contract on March 25, 2020, declaring the notice as "baseless". The same day Zhou Jie Qiong released a statement on her Weibo.

Since then, she has been promoted as an actress in China and is well-known for the dramas Miss Truth (2020), Legend of Fei (2020), To Be With You (2021) and Be My Princess (2021).
